<taxonomicName authorityName="Marsh" authorityYear="1879" box="[959,1096,1267,1293]" class="Mammalia" family="Dryolestidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="49" pageNumber="730" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Dryolestidae</taxonomicName>
indet.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="49" pageNumber="730" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="49.[959,1310,1267,1294]" box="[1172,1310,1267,1294]" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">
(
<figureCitation box="[1181,1257,1267,1294]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="50.[132,143,1593,1610]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,215,1551]" captionTargetId="figure-154@50.[698,1267,787,1361]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIG. 34. — Trechnotherian mammal teeth from the Berriasian of Angeac-Charente: A, B, left lower molar of Spalacotherium evansae Ensom &amp; Sigogneau-Russell, 2000 (ANG M-26) in occlusal (A) and lingual (B) views;C, D, left lower molar (m1 or?m2) of Dryolestidae indet.(ANG M-05) in occlusal (C) and linguodistal (D) views; E, F, left lower molar (m6 or?m7) of Dryolestidae indet. (ANG M-01) in occlusal (E) and mesial (F) views; G-I, left lower molar (m3?) of Peramus sp. (ANG M-25) in occlusal (G) labial (H) and lingual (I) views. Scale bars: 400 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902117" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902117/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
C-F)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[810,1457,1332,2028]" box="[813,952,1332,1358]" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[810,1457,1332,2028]" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marsh" authorityYear="1879" box="[813,945,1363,1389]" class="Mammalia" family="Dryolestidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="49" pageNumber="730" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Dryolestidae</taxonomicName>
are represented by only two fragmentary molars lacking the roots and the talonid (
<figureCitation box="[1177,1251,1395,1421]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="50.[132,143,1593,1610]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,215,1551]" captionTargetId="figure-154@50.[698,1267,787,1361]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIG. 34. — Trechnotherian mammal teeth from the Berriasian of Angeac-Charente: A, B, left lower molar of Spalacotherium evansae Ensom &amp; Sigogneau-Russell, 2000 (ANG M-26) in occlusal (A) and lingual (B) views;C, D, left lower molar (m1 or?m2) of Dryolestidae indet.(ANG M-05) in occlusal (C) and linguodistal (D) views; E, F, left lower molar (m6 or?m7) of Dryolestidae indet. (ANG M-01) in occlusal (E) and mesial (F) views; G-I, left lower molar (m3?) of Peramus sp. (ANG M-25) in occlusal (G) labial (H) and lingual (I) views. Scale bars: 400 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902117" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902117/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
C-F). Based on the configuration of the trigonid and the lack of a cuspid in median position on the labial side of the molars,those teeth are considered to be left lower molars (Kielan-Jaworowska 
<emphasis box="[1269,1320,1491,1517]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">et al.</emphasis>
2004). Both lower molars are shorter mesiodistally than wide labiolingually, but the most posterior molar(ANG M-01; 
<figureCitation box="[1235,1303,1554,1581]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="50.[132,143,1593,1610]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,215,1551]" captionTargetId="figure-154@50.[698,1267,787,1361]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIG. 34. — Trechnotherian mammal teeth from the Berriasian of Angeac-Charente: A, B, left lower molar of Spalacotherium evansae Ensom &amp; Sigogneau-Russell, 2000 (ANG M-26) in occlusal (A) and lingual (B) views;C, D, left lower molar (m1 or?m2) of Dryolestidae indet.(ANG M-05) in occlusal (C) and linguodistal (D) views; E, F, left lower molar (m6 or?m7) of Dryolestidae indet. (ANG M-01) in occlusal (E) and mesial (F) views; G-I, left lower molar (m3?) of Peramus sp. (ANG M-25) in occlusal (G) labial (H) and lingual (I) views. Scale bars: 400 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902117" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902117/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">Fig.34</figureCitation>
E-F)is strongly shortened and widened compared to the anterior molar (ANG M-05; 
<figureCitation box="[886,1015,1618,1645]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="50.[132,143,1593,1610]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,215,1551]" captionTargetId="figure-154@50.[698,1267,787,1361]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIG. 34. — Trechnotherian mammal teeth from the Berriasian of Angeac-Charente: A, B, left lower molar of Spalacotherium evansae Ensom &amp; Sigogneau-Russell, 2000 (ANG M-26) in occlusal (A) and lingual (B) views;C, D, left lower molar (m1 or?m2) of Dryolestidae indet.(ANG M-05) in occlusal (C) and linguodistal (D) views; E, F, left lower molar (m6 or?m7) of Dryolestidae indet. (ANG M-01) in occlusal (E) and mesial (F) views; G-I, left lower molar (m3?) of Peramus sp. (ANG M-25) in occlusal (G) labial (H) and lingual (I) views. Scale bars: 400 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902117" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902117/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">Fig. 34C, D</figureCitation>
). This feature is diagnostic of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Kielan-Jaworowska et al. 2004)" baseAuthorityName="Kielan-Jaworowska" baseAuthorityYear="2004" class="Mammalia" family="Dryolestidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="49" pageNumber="730" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">
Dryolestidae (Kielan-Jaworowska 
<emphasis box="[1023,1071,1650,1676]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">et al.</emphasis>
2004)
</taxonomicName>
. The trigonid is well-developed in both lower molars.The paraconid of the posterior molar ANG M-01 is broken at its base, but it is labiolingually more elongated than the metaconid. Both are separated by a narrow incision (
<figureCitation box="[821,912,1778,1804]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="50.[132,143,1593,1610]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,215,1551]" captionTargetId="figure-154@50.[698,1267,787,1361]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIG. 34. — Trechnotherian mammal teeth from the Berriasian of Angeac-Charente: A, B, left lower molar of Spalacotherium evansae Ensom &amp; Sigogneau-Russell, 2000 (ANG M-26) in occlusal (A) and lingual (B) views;C, D, left lower molar (m1 or?m2) of Dryolestidae indet.(ANG M-05) in occlusal (C) and linguodistal (D) views; E, F, left lower molar (m6 or?m7) of Dryolestidae indet. (ANG M-01) in occlusal (E) and mesial (F) views; G-I, left lower molar (m3?) of Peramus sp. (ANG M-25) in occlusal (G) labial (H) and lingual (I) views. Scale bars: 400 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902117" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902117/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">Fig.34E</figureCitation>
). The metaconid is enlarged and almost as high as the protoconid (
<figureCitation box="[945,1036,1810,1836]" captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="50.[132,143,1593,1610]" captionTargetBox="[132,1455,215,1551]" captionTargetId="figure-154@50.[698,1267,787,1361]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIG. 34. — Trechnotherian mammal teeth from the Berriasian of Angeac-Charente: A, B, left lower molar of Spalacotherium evansae Ensom &amp; Sigogneau-Russell, 2000 (ANG M-26) in occlusal (A) and lingual (B) views;C, D, left lower molar (m1 or?m2) of Dryolestidae indet.(ANG M-05) in occlusal (C) and linguodistal (D) views; E, F, left lower molar (m6 or?m7) of Dryolestidae indet. (ANG M-01) in occlusal (E) and mesial (F) views; G-I, left lower molar (m3?) of Peramus sp. (ANG M-25) in occlusal (G) labial (H) and lingual (I) views. Scale bars: 400 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902117" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902117/files/figure.png" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">Fig. 34F</figureCitation>
). Based on these features, the dryolestid molars from Angeac-Charente seem more closely related to either 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Martin" authorityYear="1999" box="[878,1022,1873,1899]" class="Mammalia" family="Dryolestidae" genus="Guimarotodus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="49" pageNumber="730" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[878,1022,1873,1899]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">Guimarotodus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Kimmeridgian of Guimarota in 
<collectingCountry box="[812,900,1905,1931]" name="Portugal" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">Portugal</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Martin" box="[917,1053,1905,1931]" firstAuthor="Martin" pageId="49" pageNumber="730" pagination="1 - 119" refId="ref43478" refString="MARTIN T. 1999. - Dryolestidae (Dryolestoidea, Mammalia) aus dem Oberen Jura-von Portugal. Abhandlungen der senckenbergischen naturforschenden Gesellschaft 550: 1 - 119." type="journal article" year="1999">Martin 1999</bibRefCitation>
) or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Owen" authorityYear="1871" box="[1102,1215,1905,1931]" class="Mammalia" family="Dryolestidae" genus="Phascolestes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="49" pageNumber="730" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1102,1215,1905,1931]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">Phascolestes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Berriasian of 
<collectingRegion box="[814,884,1938,1964]" country="United Kingdom" name="Dorset" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">Dorset</collectingRegion>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[913,1000,1937,1963]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">England</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Owen" box="[1011,1132,1937,1963]" firstAuthor="Owen" pageId="49" pageNumber="730" refId="ref45307" refString="OWEN R. 1871. - Monograph of the Fossil Mammalia of the Mesozoic Formations. The Palaeontographical society, London: 1 - 115 (Monograph of the Palaeontological Society; 24). https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 14831" type="journal volume" year="1871">Owen 1871</bibRefCitation>
; Kielan-Jaworowska 
<emphasis box="[1343,1390,1937,1963]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="730">et al.</emphasis>
2004) than any other 
<taxonomicName box="[977,1113,1969,1995]" class="Mammalia" family="Dryolestidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="49" pageNumber="730" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Dryolestidae</taxonomicName>
. However, additional material is required to allow a more accurate attribution.
</paragraph>
